What you need to know:  The defensive midfielder, who has been on the sidelines for six weeks, resumed training last week after suffering a hamstring-quadriceps injury in the 1-0 win over  Nairobi City Stars on January 4Mukangula's absence has been a big setback for coach Patrick Aussems, but his return has coincided with the club’s good form that has seen Ingwe register five wins, two draws and two losses from nine matchesLeopards will however be without the much-improved defender Robert Mudenyo who was injured in training two weeks ago